5:
My apologies, but may I ask
something of you?
9:
Of course you can. Friends help
friends out, after all. So what's up?
12: There is somewhere I wish to go.
18:
Where are we? This place looks like
it was abandoned a long time ago...
26:
I heard it was destroyed by a
kingdom attack a long time ago.
28: I wished to see it at least once.
39: This is where Rashid and I grew up.
41:
...Though I guess I shouldn't be
surprised that you didn't know.
49:
I let my sentiments get the best of
me. That's why I'm here.
55:
I appreciate your help back then.
Without you, I would not be here
now.
58:
Save your thanks. I was only doing it
to help Rashid.
61:
Honestly... I still think it best to cut
you down where you stand.
63:
We should never risk having another
Titan rise up again.
66:
You've proven you're too easy to
manipulate.
70:
...I will never do such a thing again.
Nor will I allow myself to be forced to.
73:
Right. That'll definitely be the case
after I finish you off.
76:
I will not allow you to take this life
that Rashid risked everything to
protect.
83: I do owe you an apology.
87:
You were correct to say I am
dangerous... If I had not been by
Rashid's side, then perhaps he
would still be...
91: ...No, I was speaking out of anger.
93:
Now that I think about it... If I had
never left Rashid's side, then he
would have never met you in the
first place.
102:
What a coincidence. I don't like you
either.
106:
...Hoo, I can practically see the
sparks fly.
109:
It's understandable, isn't it? They
were enemies when they met, which
isn't easy to forget even though
things have changed...
113:
Ha. You've never seen two people
fighting over a man before, have
you?
140:
I guess it's one thing to know, and
another to see it with your own eyes.
142:
You probably weren't ready for this
yet, huh...
147: N-no, thank you... for showing me...
157:
...I'll be waiting to see the day you
fulfill Rashid's last wish.
161:
And you... better... preserve the
borderlands... so my journey is not in
vain...
183:
When you gave me your last order,
I...
190:
The worlds out there are bigger...
and far more beautiful than I
thought.
192:
I have only started my journey... but
one day, I will come to understand...
199: I shall be going now, Rashid.
201:
But one day, I will return.
And when I do...
